header.gameNote: LAS VEGAS HOLIDAY HOOPS CLASSIC AT LAS VEGAS NV

article.headline: Akron 75, Ark.-Little Rock 61
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- Darryl Roberts scored 16 points to lead Akron to a 75-61 victory over Arkansas-Little Rock on Tuesday at the Las Vegas Holiday Hoops Classic. Akron (6-4), which owned a 46-31 halftime lead, also had Zeke Marshall with 14 points and 16 rebounds, Brett McClanahan with 14 points and Alex Abreu with 10. Arkansas-Little Rock (6-6) was led by Solomon Bozeman with 19 points. Courtney Jackson and Alex Garcia-Mendoza added 10 points each for the Trojans. The Zips shot 50.0 percent (28 of 56) from the field and did even better from 3-point range, hitting 11 of 21 for 52.4 percent. The Trojans were limited to 39.1 percent shooting (18 of 46).
